description: At a Congress Working Committee meeting, Rahul Gandhi emphasized the party's inclusive stance, advocating for the representation of all communities without reservation. Discussions encompassed political strategy, the Palestine-Israel conflict, and social justice issues like caste census. Shashi Tharoor urged constructive criticism, while Manish Tewari voiced concerns about Chinese encroachment.
title: Appropriated by BJP, Congress tries to reclaim Patel legacy

description: The Supreme Court overturned the Calcutta High Court's order for a CBI probe into the West Bengal cabinet's decision to create supernumerary teacher posts in May 2022. The court emphasized that scrutinizing cabinet decisions with criminality undermines federalism, especially when no appointments were made based on that decision.
title: Can’t attach criminality to state cabinet decision: SC on WB teacher posts

description: In an unprecedented move, the Supreme Court has deemed 10 Tamil Nadu bills, long delayed by the governor, as assented. The court criticized the governor's actions as unconstitutional, setting strict timelines for governors to approve or reject state bills. Assent must be granted within a month, with a three-month window for reconsideration or presidential referral.
title: SC sets timeline for state governors to decide on bills sent to them

description: A public feud has erupted within the Trinamool Congress (TMC) following veteran MP Sougata Ray's criticism of Kalyan Banerjee. Banerjee retaliated with a barrage of accusations against unnamed party members, including allegations of improper conduct towards BSF personnel and questioning integrity.
title: TMC LS chief whip Kalyan Banerjee attacks colleagues, no holds barred

description: The Uttarakhand High Court has criticized the excise commissioner for not renewing liquor licenses of six shops in Rishikesh, citing their proximity to 'holy places,' while other establishments were permitted.
title: Uttarakhand HC okays licence renewal for 6 liquor vends in Rishikesh

description: PM Modi defended the Waqf Act amendments, stating they rectify UPA's appeasement policies that favored fundamentalists and land grabbers, contributing to India's Partition. He asserted the 2013 changes prioritized land mafia interests over the Constitution, hindering justice for victims. The new law aims to protect common Muslims, with Parliament passing it after extensive debate and public consultation.
title: Waqf Act amended to neutralise changes made by Congress for 'appeasement': PM

description: The Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) has renamed the 16th-century Mughal-era Shahi Jama Masjid in Sambhal to 'Juma Masjid,' replacing the old green signboard with a new blue one. This action follows a legal dispute and communal unrest sparked by claims that the mosque was built atop a Hindu temple.
title: ASI restores 'historic name' of Sambhal's Jama Masjid

description: K Radhakrishnan, a CPM central committee member and Lok Sabha MP, was interrogated by the ED regarding a money laundering case involving the Karuvannur cooperative bank. The investigation revolves around Rs 150 crore in loans allegedly sanctioned using fraudulent documents, with cash donations purportedly made to the party in return.
title: ED quizzes Kerala CPM MP in money laundering case

description: A grenade attack at BJP leader Manoranjan Kalia's Jalandhar residence, the 22nd such incident in Punjab since September, has sparked investigations into potential ISI and Lawrence Bishnoi gang links. Two suspects are arrested for the attack, allegedly orchestrated by Zeeshan Akhtar and Pakistan-based Shahzad Bhatti. The incident led to the removal of Punjab's intelligence chief.
title: Grenade hit on BJP neta's Punjab house; cops claim role of ISI, Bishnoi, nab 2

description: V Senthil Balaji, reappointed as a minister after bail, defended his position in the Tamil Nadu cabinet before the Supreme Court, asserting his popular mandate. He argued that courts cannot constitutionally disqualify a minister and emphasized his adherence to bail conditions. Balaji highlighted that the corruption case against him began while he was already a minister, suggesting no undue influence.
title: I have mandate to be mantri, court can't chastise me: Balaji

description: PM Modi and Dubai Crown Prince Sheikh Hamdan convened to bolster the India-UAE Comprehensive Strategic Partnership, emphasizing trade, investment, defense, and technology. Discussions centered on co-development and co-production of defense equipment. Modi thanked the UAE for supporting the 4.3 million Indians residing there, acknowledging their contribution to the strong bilateral relationship.
title: PM Modi, Dubai Crown Prince focus on boosting strategic ties

description: Tahawwur Rana, the mastermind behind the 26/11 Mumbai attacks, is expected to arrive in India, prompting special security arrangements in Delhi and Mumbai jails. Rana, an LeT member, facilitated David Headley's reconnaissance for the attacks and even gloated over the casualties.
title: 26/11 mastermind Tahawwur Rana to arrive in India today, NIA to take custody first

description: Nintendo has paused Switch 2 pre-orders in Canada, initially scheduled for April 9, aligning with a similar delay in the US due to potential tariff impacts. The June 5 launch date remains unchanged. Retailers like Walmart Canada and GameStop have confirmed the pre-order delays.
title: After US, Nintendo delays Switch 2 pre-orders in Canada

description: Trump's Trade Representative, Jameson Greer, stated that India and other nations are considering lowering tariffs following new trade measures. Greer defended Trump's trade policies, citing the need for reciprocity and addressing the US trade deficit. He highlighted the decline in manufacturing jobs and the administration's commitment to reversing industrial decline through these trade adjustments.
title: India among nations ready to lower tariffs under Trump policy: US trade rep
White House confirms 104% tariffs on China goes into effect starting today

description: Paul Skenes will face Sonny Gray as the Pittsburgh Pirates aim to extend their winning streak against the St. Louis Cardinals. Skenes, coming off a Rookie of the Year season, seeks his first win against St. Louis, while Gray hopes to improve after mixed results.
title: Will Paul Skenes play tonight against the Cardinals? Latest update

description: In Jaipur, a tragic incident unfolded on Nahargarh Road as an SUV driven by Congress official Usman Khan ran over nine people, resulting in three fatalities and six injuries. Khan, allegedly speeding at 70km/h, collided with multiple vehicles over a 500m stretch.
title: 3 killed, 6 injured as Congress leader ploughs SUV into crowd in Jaipur

description: Meghalaya's Principal Secretary, Syed Md A Razi, was found dead in his Uzbekistan hotel room on Monday, suspected of cardiac arrest. Razi, an IRTS officer on deputation since 2021, was in Bukhara on a personal trip. Hotel staff discovered him after he didn't respond to calls. His wife is traveling to Uzbekistan to retrieve his remains.
title: Meghalaya principal secy found dead in Uzbek hotel

description: Tahawwur Rana, a key planner of the 2008 Mumbai terror attacks, is being extradited to India by US authorities after his final appeal was rejected. He is expected to arrive in India soon and will be formally arrested.
title: Rana loses his last ditch bid to thwart extradition to India
Trump will be incredibly gracious if China reaches out but...: White House on 104% tariff

description: Sanjay Bhandari, accused of tax evasion and money laundering, has won his extradition battle against the Indian government in the UK. The UK high court denied Delhi's final appeal to extradite him, citing concerns about potential human rights violations and a fair trial in India.
title: UK court junks India plea, arms dealer Bhandari now free man

description: Elon Musk's efforts to persuade Donald Trump to halt new tariffs failed, despite his significant financial support and influence. Trump not only ignored Musk's pleas but escalated the situation, threatening additional tariffs on Chinese imports. This public disagreement highlights a growing rift between the business world and Trump's protectionist trade policies, raising concerns about the economic fallout.
title: Tariff war: Inside Elon Musk’s personal appeal to Donald Trump - and why it failed

description: Priyansh Arya's explosive century propelled Punjab Kings to a thrilling 18-run victory over Chennai Super Kings. Arya's breathtaking 103 off 42 balls, including nine sixes, lifted PBKS from a precarious position to a commanding 219/6. Despite Conway's 69 and Dhoni's late fireworks, CSK fell short, as Arya's onslaught proved decisive, snapping PBKS's losing streak.
title: IPL: Priyansh Arya's stunning ton powers Punjab Kings past Chennai Super Kings
Mexico reports first human death from H5N1 bird flu

description: Jammu and Kashmir's assembly witnessed turmoil for the second day as opposition parties moved a no-confidence motion against Speaker Abdul Rahim Rather over a Waqf law debate. Despite calls from his own party, National Conference, for flexibility, Rather insisted assembly rules prohibited discussion on the sub-judice matter.
title: No-trust move against J&K Speaker over Waqf debate ‘gag’

description: Pakistan's political arena is witnessing a fierce power struggle among the military, Imran Khan, and Shehbaz Sharif's government, further complicated by US foreign policy and the Pakistani diaspora's growing influence. Khan, alleging a US-backed conspiracy, challenges the status quo from prison, while Sharif grapples with economic woes and security threats amidst a legitimacy crisis.
title: Pakistan: Military, Imran Khan, Shehbaz Sharif clash amid US, diaspora influence

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah chaired security and development review meetings in Srinagar, reiterating the government's zero-tolerance policy against terrorism and urging coordinated efforts to eliminate it. He lauded the reduction in terror activities and emphasized the commitment to lasting peace and development in Jammu and Kashmir.
title: Shah asks security agencies to work in ‘mission mode’ to make J&K terror-free

description: The hacker group DonRoad Team, previously targeting Donald Trump's websites, has threatened cyberattacks on Elon Musk's companies, including Tesla, SpaceX, and X. They announced plans to disrupt Musk-related sites for a month, potentially impacting X, Grok, and Tesla.
title: ‘Suspending all websites affiliated with Musk,’ say hackers who hit Trump
Usha Vance breaks silence on 'normalizing Indian hate', says she thinks it's terrible

description: Khaleel Ahmed delivered a fiery performance for Chennai Super Kings against Punjab Kings, dismissing Shreyas Iyer with a stunning delivery. Ahmed's raw, emotional celebration ignited the CSK camp after the crucial wicket. Despite an expensive first over, Khaleel bounced back, showcasing his ability to strike at key moments and bring passion to the pitch, solidifying his importance to Chennai.
title: Aggressive Khaleel Ahmed roars at Shreyas in animated send-off
BJP suspends leader for 'purifying' temple after Dalit MLA's visit

description: The Centre has filed a caveat in the Supreme Court, seeking a hearing before any ruling on petitions challenging the Waqf (Amendment) Act, 2025. Several petitions, including those from Asaduddin Owaisi and the All India Muslim Personal Law Board, contest the Act, which aims to improve waqf property management. The petitions are likely to be heard before April 15.
title: Centre seeks urgent hearing in SC before ruling on pleas against Waqf Act

description: At the Congress Working Committee meeting in Ahmedabad, P. Chidambaram fainted due to the heat at Sabarmati Ashram and was quickly hospitalized. Congress leaders nationwide convened in Gujarat, a state unconquered for 30 years, to strategize future political moves. The AICC's 84th National Convention, a first for Gujarat in 64 years, addresses key national issues, internal organization, and election preparations.
title: Cong leader P Chidambaram faints due to heat in Ahmedabad, rushed to hospital

description: As the Congress Working Committee convenes in Ahmedabad to strategize for upcoming elections, former leader Sanjay Jha proposes a five-point action plan to revitalize the party. Jha's recommendations include forming a shadow cabinet, decentralizing the party's structure with regional vice-presidents, and creating a model state of governance to showcase the Congress's capabilities.
title: CWC meet: '5 things Congress should do to revive party'

description: A scam in Malhar village, Yadgir, has been exposed where men disguised as women submitted fabricated attendance photos to fraudulently claim Rs 3 lakh in MGNREGA benefits. The deceptive scheme involved uploading images via NMMS, falsely indicating female worker participation in canal dredging work at Pujari's farm.
title: Draped in sarees, men pose as women to claim MGNREGA benefits in Karnataka
Elon Musk calls Trump tariff adviser 'dumber than a sack of bricks'

description: Elon Musk's net worth plummeted below $300 billion following a sharp decline in Tesla's stock price, triggered by President Trump's newly imposed tariffs on imported goods and foreign cars. Other billionaires, including Mark Zuckerberg, Jeff Bezos, and Jensen Huang, also experienced significant wealth losses due to the market turmoil. Musk has publicly criticized the tariffs and trade advisor Peter Navarro.
title: Elon Musk’s net worth falls below $300 billion; here’s how much he lost in 2025 so far

description: The Donald Trump administration has till now shown no inclination to blink on the implementation of the reciprocal tariffs. They have however, shown openness to negotiate with countries, and India is already working on a trade deal with the US. If no imminent relief on tariffs is on the horizon, what should the world do? What should India do to counter the impact of Trump’s reciprocal tariffs?
title: Explained: How unfair are Trump’s tariffs, and what is India’s relative advantage

description: TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee accused Kirti Azad of leaking internal party conversations regarding a public spat at the Election Commission. Banerjee admitted to the altercation but blamed Azad for provoking him and sharing WhatsApp chats.
title: Feud within TMC? Kalyan Banerjee blames Kirti Azad for leaking 'infighting' WhatsApp chats

description: The Freestyle Chess Grand Slam preliminary stage wrapped up in Paris. Ian Nepomniachtchi and Magnus Carlsen led with 8.5 points each. Nepomniachtchi secured the top spot via tiebreaks. Maxime Vachier-Lagrave finished third. Arjun Erigaisi and Nodirbek Abdusattorov also advanced. Hikaru Nakamura qualified after a tough endgame. Gukesh Dommaraju was eliminated. Vincent Keymer's victory secured his place.
title: Gukesh out! World champion falls in Paris Freestyle Chess prelims

description: Nicholas Pooran's explosive, unbeaten 87 off 36 balls propelled Lucknow Super Giants to a thrilling four-run victory over Kolkata Knight Riders in IPL 2025. Pooran's milestone innings, reaching 2,000 IPL runs in record time, helped LSG post a formidable 238/3. Despite valiant efforts from Rahane and Rinku Singh, KKR fell just short of the target.
title: IPL 2025: Pooran's milestone mayhem helps LSG sink KKR

description: First, scientists dug up some old bones. Fossils, actually — real direwolf teeth and skulls buried in the earth for 13,000 to 72,000 years. These bones still had tiny fragments of DNA inside — think of DNA as the instruction manual for building a creature. Of course, ancient DNA is like a book that’s been through a shredder and then set on fire, but with a lot of tech and patience, scientists can piece together a decent draft.
title: Is Jon Snow's 'best friend' back from extinction?

description: Kolkata Knight Riders captain Ajinkya Rahane expressed concerns about the Eden Gardens pitch. He noted its lack of support for spinners after a loss to Lucknow Super Giants. Rahane hinted at potential issues with 'home advantage'. KKR lost their second home game. The match saw a high-scoring affair. Rahane's strategy to bowl first did not work.
title: 'Kuch bolunga toh bawal ho jayega': Rahane reignites pitch controversy

description: Mumbai experienced a high of 36.2°C with significant humidity, leading to a road near the BMC headquarters appearing to melt. Jalgaon recorded the state's highest temperature at 42.5°C. The IMD has issued a yellow alert for Mumbai, cautioning about heat-related illnesses, especially for vulnerable populations, as dry, warm easterly winds fuel the heatwave expected to last until Wednesday.
title: Mumbai heatwave: Road near BMC headquarters ‘melts' as temperature soars

description: MS Dhoni achieved another milestone in his illustrious IPL career, becoming the first wicket-keeper to complete 150 catches. The CSK veteran reached this feat during a match against Punjab Kings, solidifying his legacy as an impactful player. Despite Punjab Kings' high score, Dhoni's sharp glovework stood out, proving his continued excellence and cementing his status as one of the greatest.
title: New Record! MS Dhoni becomes first player to ...

description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) declared a Rs 3 billion earning from hosting the ICC Champions Trophy, surpassing their Rs 2 billion target. Amid concerns over the national team's performance, the PCB defended its financial decisions, stating the ICC managed the tournament. Stadium upgrades are underway with Rs 18 billion investment, targeting completion by 2026.
title: 'Pakistan earns Rs 3 billion from Champions Trophy, surpasses targets'

description: Salim Akhtar, a prominent producer of Hindi films, is no more. He produced successful films like 'Phool Aur Angaare' and 'Qayamat'. Salim Akhtar died in Mumbai on April 8. The details of his death are unknown. This news comes after the recent death of Manoj Kumar. Salim Akhtar is survived by his wife, Shama Akhtar, and son, Samad Akhtar.
title: Rani Mukerji's 'Raja Ki Aayegi Baraat' producer Salim Akhtar passes away

description: Sachin Tendulkar, the 'God of Cricket', recently visited Assam's Kaziranga National Park, enjoying a jeep safari and interacting with a young fan. His illustrious career, spanning from 1989 to 2013, includes a record-breaking 34,357 international runs and 100 centuries. A key player in India's 2011 World Cup victory, Tendulkar also led the Mumbai Indians to an IPL title in 2013.
title: Sachin Tendulkar visits Kaziranga National Park - Watch

description: In a symbolic move, the Congress party convened a CWC meeting at the Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel Museum in Ahmedabad, aiming to reclaim Patel's legacy. Mallikarjun Kharge criticized the BJP-RSS for appropriating Patel's heritage, highlighting Patel's ban on the RSS and emphasizing the close relationship between Patel and Nehru. The party seeks to counter the narrative of Congress sidelining Patel.
title: 'Sardar Patel in our thoughts': How Congress is reclaiming Iron Man's legacy

description: In a bizarre turn, Shardul Thakur bowled five consecutive wides in a crucial over against Kolkata Knight Riders. Lucknow Super Giants skipper Rishabh Pant was visibly frustrated. Thakur's wayward bowling eased the pressure on KKR during their chase of a massive target. Despite the extras, Thakur eventually dismissed Ajinkya Rahane.
title: Shardul bowls 5 consecutive wides, leaves Pant frustrated
‘She was crying’: TMC’s Saugata Roy says Mahua broke down after spat with Kalyan

description: China urges India to unite against the US's tariff abuse, emphasizing the need for multilateralism and opposing protectionism. Despite trade tensions and Trump's threat of increased tariffs, China defends its economic system and commitment to global trade. China also hinted retaliatory measures against the US to protect its interests amid escalating trade disputes.
title: 'Should stand together': China invites India to fight against 'US tariff abuse'

description: South Korean troops fired warning shots after North Korean soldiers briefly crossed the heavily fortified border. The North Korean troops, some armed and wearing protective gear, were detected within the demilitarized zone. This incident follows increased North Korean military activity near the border, including terrain clearing and barbed wire installation, amid heightened tensions and political changes in South Korea.
title: South Korea fires warning shots as North Korean soldiers violate border
Suchir Balaji's parents claim he was shot twice in the head
US and China rift widens amid insults and mind games
Waqf Amendment Act 2025 comes into force from April 8
Waqf protest turns violent in Bengal's Murshidabad

description: Priyansh Arya, the 24-year-old Delhi batter, blasted a stunning century for Punjab Kings against Chennai Super Kings in IPL 2025, reaching the milestone in just 39 balls. Co-owner Preity Zinta's ecstatic celebration went viral as Arya's explosive innings, built on prior success in the Delhi Premier League and Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy, etched his name in IPL history.
title: Watch: Preity Zinta's wild celebration breaks internet after Arya ton

description: Lucknow Super Giants' spinner Digvesh Rathi grabbed attention by dismissing his idol, Sunil Narine, in a recent match against Kolkata Knight Riders. Rathi celebrated the crucial wicket with a unique gesture, signing the grass, a departure from his controversial 'notebook' celebration. This respectful act followed previous fines for excessive exuberance.
title: Watch: Rathi shows off new celebration after hero Narine's wicket

description: Priyansh Arya, the 24-year-old Delhi batter, has burst onto the IPL scene with a stunning 42-ball century for Punjab Kings against Chennai Super Kings. His explosive innings, the second-fastest by an Indian in IPL history, follows a trail of impressive performances, including a blistering knock in the Delhi Premier League and a century in the Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy.
title: Who is Priyansh Arya, 2nd-fastest Indian to score IPL century

description: For centuries, the West has sought to decode the universe with the rigour of Euclid and the certainty of Christ. But every so often, reality throws up a figure so fundamentally resistant to analysis, so wildly entangled in contradictions, that it defies all classical tools of understanding — and instead demands a quantum lens. Donald Trump is one such figure. Not a politician in the traditional sense, nor a businessman in any useful one, he is an event horizon of logic. A paradox with a golf handicap. And like all good paradoxes, he doesn’t need to make sense — only impact.
title: Why only Salman Khan can explain Trump tariffs
Why Uddhav Sena is looking to revive itself in Maharashtra through Konkan

description: Global temperatures soared to historic highs in March, continuing an unprecedented heat streak that challenges scientific understanding. Europe experienced its hottest March ever, leading to extreme rainfall variations. The world marked its second-hottest March, sustaining record-breaking temperatures since July 2023, with scientists noting the persistent anomaly and its link to human-caused climate change.
title: World's 'exceptional' heat streak lengthens into March

description: President Zelenskyy announced the capture of two Chinese nationals fighting for Russia in Ukraine's Donetsk region, possessing identification and bank cards. Ukraine is investigating the presence of more Chinese citizens within Russian units, signaling concerns about China's involvement and Putin's intentions to prolong the war. Kyiv seeks clarification from Beijing and expects a response from allies regarding this development.
title: Zelenskyy claims Ukraine captured two Chinese nationals fighting for Russia

description: Kayla Nicole is opening up about the emotional challenges she faced while dating high-profile men, including Travis Kelce, revealing the toxic dynamics and public scrutiny that took a toll on her. She emphasizes the importance of prioritizing self-love and setting boundaries after experiencing harsh treatment and online harassment. Now, Kayla is choosing privacy and emotional safety in her relationships.
title: Kayla Nicole says Travis Kelce isn't the only one who has caused her pain

description: Despite Mumbai Indians' loss to Royal Challengers Bengaluru, Rohit Sharma's playful mimicry of the 'X' substitution gesture brought smiles to fans. While his batting performance remained underwhelming, with an early dismissal for 17, his light-hearted moment went viral. The match saw RCB clinch a 12-run victory, fueled by Kohli and Patidar's half-centuries, despite valiant efforts from Varma and Pandya.
title: Watch: Rohit hilariously mimics umpire with 'X' signal
Will Trump’s tariffs trigger a recession in US? Signs economists are watching closely

description: The ACLU-NH has filed a lawsuit against the US Department of Homeland Security on behalf of a Chinese doctoral student at Dartmouth College whose F-1 student status was abruptly terminated without explanation. The lawsuit alleges violation of due process rights, as the student met all requirements for maintaining his status.
title: International students in US file lawsuits over visa termination status

description: Vaniya Agrawal, an Indian-American software engineer, resigned from Microsoft after protesting the company's alleged role in providing AI technology to Israel's military. She disrupted Microsoft's 50th-anniversary celebration, accusing the company of enabling violence in Gaza. Agrawal cited a $133 million contract with Israel's Ministry of Defense and urged employees to sign the "No Azure for Apartheid" petition before her dismissal.
title: Vaniya Agrawal, who disrupted Microsoft’s event shares resignation email sent

description: Indian entrepreneur Shruti Chaturvedi alleges she and a companion were detained for eight hours at Anchorage Airport, Alaska, over a 'suspicious' power bank. Chaturvedi claims extensive interrogation, a physical search, and denial of basic rights occurred. She states the FBI and local police questioned them before releasing them without charges, confiscating her luggage.
title: 'Physically checked by male, denied restroom': Indian's 8-hour US airport ordeal

description: N John Camm, posing as Dr. Narendra Vikramaditya Yadav, was arrested for allegedly causing seven patient deaths at Damoh's Mission Hospital. He performed 13 surgeries and examined 70 patients during his two-month tenure, earning a high salary. Investigations revealed his medical registration was invalid, and he lacked proper credentials, raising concerns about hospital hiring practices and oversight.
title: MP 'doctor' who caused death of 7 patients was drawing Rs 8 lakh monthly salary

description: Belief in witchcraft persists globally, with a significant portion of the population convinced of its existence. While historical witch hunts targeted vulnerable individuals, modern witches embrace nature-based religions and seek personal empowerment. However, experts caution against romanticizing the past and highlight the dangers of unchecked belief in the supernatural, drawing parallels to contemporary conspiracy theories.
title: Why do many people still believe in witches?

description: The Supreme Court has strongly criticized Tamil Nadu governor RN Ravi for withholding assent to Bills passed by the state assembly. The court declared that the governor's actions, including reserving 10 Bills for the President after they were already reconsidered, were illegal and unconstitutional. The court declared these Bills as passed.
title: 'Should not act as per political expediency': SC slams TN guv for 'sitting over' bills

description: As trade tensions escalate, President Xi Jinping adopts a confrontational stance against US tariffs, signaling readiness for a prolonged trade war. Beijing retaliates with duties and prepares for economic resilience, while Trump aims to address the trade deficit and appeal to voters. The global markets face turmoil, and analysts warn of potential economic fallout.
title: Tariff war: Trump escalates, Xi digs in — who will blink first?

description: Fannie Mae laid off 700 employees, with about 200 terminations, primarily of Telugu origin, due to ethical violations related to the misuse of the 'matching grants program'. Employees allegedly colluded with non-profits like TANA, mirroring a similar scam at Apple where employees were fired for exploiting the company's charitable donation matching program.
title: American company sacks 700, of these 200 in 'donation scam'

description: Donald Trump proposed US control over Gaza, envisioning its transformation into a thriving hub and suggesting the relocation of its residents. While Netanyahu acknowledged the need for a new approach, Arab nations rejected the resettlement plan. Leaders from France, Jordan, and Egypt advocated for Palestinian Authority control, a proposal Israel previously dismissed.
title: ‘Incredible real estate’: Trump revives Gaza plan during talks with Netanyahu

description: US authorities are now revoking visas of Indian students for minor offenses, including traffic violations, after previously targeting them for alleged campus activism. Dozens have received notices from their schools, citing past incidents like lane shifting, drunk driving, and shoplifting as reasons for immediate departure.
title: Minor offences come back to haunt Indian students in US, told to self-deport

description: The US Supreme Court has granted the Trump administration temporary authority to deport Venezuelan migrants accused of gang ties under the Alien Enemies Act of 1798. While allowing fast-track deportations, the court mandated that affected individuals receive a court hearing to contest their removal. The ruling exposed divisions within the court, with dissenting justices raising concerns about bypassing judicial scrutiny.
title: Trump admin wins court approval to fast-track deportations under wartime law

description: Indian stocks with significant US market exposure are facing heavy selling pressure amid growing recession fears in the US and a potential global slowdown. Concerns over high US import tariffs and retaliatory measures are impacting sectors like auto, metals, software, and pharma.
title: Trump's tariffs: Larger the US business, bigger the stock hit
